Preheat oven to 325 degrees F. Place a large pan of hot water on bottom shelf of oven. Meanwhile, heat oil in large nonstick skillet on medium heat. Add mushrooms and garlic. Cook and stir 5 min. or until softened; drain. Beat cream cheese, sour cream and cayenne pepper in large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing on low speed after each addition just until blended. Stir in mushroom mixture and rosemary until blended. Pour into greased 9-inch springform pan. Bake 30 to 35 min. or until centre is almost set. Cool completely. Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight. Remove from pan.